main event: An unidentified flying object was tracked on radar for approximately 45 minutes over the central Pacific Ocean on April 9, 1963.
interesting points: The object was tracked at an altitude of 42,000 feet and a range of approximately 100 nautical miles.
The object maintained a constant bearing of 270 degrees and elevation of 5 degrees during the observation period.
The report notes that the size of the object was similar to a 'pin', suggesting it was a relatively small object.
No further information or evaluation of the object is provided in the report.
The report was generated by the Office of the Director of Intelligence at Wright-Patterson Air Force Base.
